---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import Header from '../components/Header.astro'
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro'
---

<Base title="Terms of Service — Extol">
  <Header />

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-600 text-bark-900 mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-warm-gray-400 mb-1"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 2026</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-warm-gray-400 mb-1"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> March 2026</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-warm-gray-400 mb-1"><strong>Entity:</strong> Extol, Inc., a Wyoming corporation</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-warm-gray-400 mb-12"><strong>Contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:legal@extol.work" class="text-terracotta-500 underline">legal@extol.work</a></p>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing or using the Extol platform, including the Brij community
        event tool and any associated services (collectively, the "Services"),
        you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not
        agree to these Terms, do not use the Services.
      </p>
      <p>
        "We," "us," and "Extol" refer to Extol, Inc. "You" and "your" refer to
        the individual or entity accessing the Services.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Description of Services</h2>

      <h3>2.1 Brij</h3>
      <p>Brij is a community event coordination tool that enables:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Creation and management of community events</li>
        <li>Attendance tracking and check-in</li>
        <li>Recording of contributions and activities</li>
        <li>Peer attestations within communities</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Brij is available as open-source software under the Apache License 2.0.
        The hosted version of Brij on the Extol platform is subject to these
        Terms.
      </p>

      <h3>2.2 Extol Platform</h3>
      <p>
        The Extol platform provides governance infrastructure for voluntary
        communities, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Community formation and governance tools</li>
        <li>Collective organization under the Contributor Commons Agreement (CCA)</li>
        <li>On-chain attestations on the Solana blockchain</li>
        <li>Community governance tokens</li>
        <li>Cross-community reputation (Tempo)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2.3 Free and Paid Tiers</h3>
      <p>
        Certain features of the Services are available at no charge. Premium
        features are available through paid subscription plans as described on
        our pricing page. We reserve the right to modify pricing with 30 days'
        advance notice.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Account Registration</h2>

      <h3>3.1 Account Creation</h3>
      <p>
        To use certain features of the Services, you must create an account.
        You agree to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide accurate and complete registration information</li>
        <li>Maintain the security of your account credentials</li>
        <li>Promptly update your information if it changes</li>
        <li>Accept responsibility for all activity under your account</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3.2 Age Requirements</h3>
      <p>
        You must be at least 13 years old to create an account or use the
        Services. If you are between 13 and 18, you represent that your parent
        or legal guardian has reviewed and agreed to these Terms on your behalf.
      </p>
      <p>
        For communities that serve participants under 13, additional parental
        consent requirements apply. See our COPPA Compliance section (Section
        11).
      </p>

      <h3>3.3 Coordinator Accounts</h3>
      <p>
        Community coordinators who record attendance or activities on behalf of
        other participants represent that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The participant actually participated in the recorded event</li>
        <li>They have a good-faith basis for creating records on the
          participant's behalf</li>
        <li>They understand the participant will be notified and may review or
          delete the record</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. User Content and Contributions</h2>

      <h3>4.1 Your Content</h3>
      <p>
        You retain ownership of all content you submit to the Services,
