      </p>
      <p>
        By submitting User Content, you grant Extol a non-exclusive, worldwide,
        royalty-free license to use, store, display, and process your User
        Content solely to provide and improve the Services. This license
        terminates when you delete your content or account, subject to
        Section 4.3.
      </p>

      <h3>4.2 Contributor Commons Agreement</h3>
      <p>
        If you participate in a Collective under the Contributor Commons
        Agreement (CCA), your Contributions are governed by the CCA in addition
        to these Terms. In the event of a conflict between these Terms and the
        CCA with respect to Contributions, the CCA controls.
      </p>

      <h3>4.3 On-Chain Data</h3>
      <p>
        If your community uses Extol governance features, certain data may be
        recorded as on-chain attestations on the Solana blockchain. You
        acknowledge that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>On-chain data is public and permanent — it cannot be deleted from the
          blockchain</li>
        <li>Attestations use pseudonymous wallet addresses, not your name or
          personal information</li>
        <li>Extol maintains the connection between your identity and your wallet
          address; this connection can be severed upon account deletion (see
          Section 9)</li>
        <li>On-chain attestations may include hashed records of participation,
          governance token balances, and staking positions</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>4.4 Prohibited Content</h3>
      <p>You may not submit content that:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Is unlawful, fraudulent, or deceptive</li>
        <li>Infringes any third party's intellectual property or privacy rights</li>
        <li>Contains malware or disruptive code</li>
        <li>Impersonates another person or entity</li>
        <li>Is designed to manipulate governance mechanisms or attestation scores</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Community Governance</h2>

      <h3>5.1 Community Rules</h3>
      <p>
        Individual communities may adopt governance rules (Bylaws) consistent
        with the CCA and these Terms. Community Bylaws may impose additional
        requirements on members beyond these Terms, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Contribution standards and quality requirements</li>
        <li>Governance participation expectations</li>
        <li>Membership tiers and eligibility criteria</li>
        <li>Revenue distribution formulas</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>5.2 Governance Tokens</h3>
      <p>
        Communities that issue governance tokens do so under the terms of their
        Bylaws and the CCA. Governance tokens:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Represent governance weight, not economic value</li>
        <li>Are non-transferable by default (communities may enable transfers
          through governance vote)</li>
        <li>May be subject to inflation mechanics that dilute inactive holders</li>
        <li>Are not securities, investment contracts, or financial instruments</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>5.3 Platform Governance</h3>
      <p>
        Changes to the Extol platform that affect all communities — including
        changes to these Terms, the CCA, and platform-wide policies — are
        subject to a governance process that includes Collective input, as
        described in the Platform Governance Charter.
      </p>

