      <p>
        Violation of this section may result in account suspension or
        termination.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Account Deletion and Data Removal</h2>

      <h3>9.1 Your Right to Delete</h3>
      <p>
        You may delete your account at any time through Settings. Upon
        deletion:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Brij layer:</strong> Your user record, all attendance records, contribution
        records, and peer attestations are permanently deleted.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Extol middleware:</strong> The connection between your identity and your
        blockchain wallet address is permanently severed. Your wallet becomes
        an anonymous, unlinked address.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>On-chain layer:</strong> Attestations, token balances, and staking positions
        on the public blockchain cannot be deleted. However, without the
        identity-to-wallet mapping (which has been deleted), these records
        cannot be linked back to you.
      </p>

      <h3>9.2 Irreversibility</h3>
      <p>
        Account deletion is permanent and cannot be undone. We cannot recover
        deleted accounts, activity history, or identity-to-wallet mappings.
      </p>

      <h3>9.3 Coordinator Records</h3>
      <p>
        If you delete your account, records that a coordinator created on your
        behalf are also deleted. Aggregate community statistics (e.g., total
        event attendance counts) may be retained in anonymized form.
      </p>

